🤖 AI Interview Simulator


A resume-aware interview preparation tool that generates personalized technical questions from your actual background — not generic question banks.

📌 Project Overview
---------------------
The AI Interview Simulator is a Python-based web application designed to help job seekers practice interviews in a realistic, personalized way. Unlike conventional mock-interview tools that serve pre-written questions, this simulator reads your resume and generates questions that are directly relevant to your skills, projects, and experience.
The project addresses a common pain point: candidates preparing for interviews often practice with generic questions that don't reflect what they'll actually be asked. This tool closes that gap by making preparation targeted and efficient.

🎯 Problem Statement
----------------------
Most interview prep tools rely on static question banks. This means:

Candidates practice questions irrelevant to their background
Behavioral and project-specific questions go unpracticed
There's no dynamic adaptation to what a candidate has actually built or done

Solution: Parse the candidate's resume, extract meaningful signals (skills, projects, roles), and generate tailored questions on-the-fly for a realistic interview simulation.

⚙️ How It Works
----------------
User uploads Resume (PDF / TXT)
        ↓
Resume Parser extracts:
  - Technical Skills
  - Projects & Descriptions
  - Work Experience
        ↓
Interview Engine generates:
  - Technical questions (based on skills)
  - Project-specific questions
  - Behavioral questions
        ↓
Streamlit UI presents questions one-by-one
        ↓
User answers → Receives immediate feedback

🛠️ Tech Stack
----------------
LayerTechnologyPurposeFrontend / UIStreamlitInteractive web interface, no HTML/CSS neededBackend LogicPython 3.7+Resume parsing, question generation enginePDF ParsingPyPDF2Extracting text from uploaded PDF resumesFile HandlingPython io / osSupporting TXT and PDF resume formats

🗂️ Project Structure
AI-Interview-Simulator/
│
├── app.py                  # Main Streamlit app — UI and user flow
├── resume_parser.py        # Parses PDF/TXT resumes; extracts skills, projects, experience
├── interview_engine.py     # Core question generation logic
└── README.md               # Project documentation

Module Responsibilities
-----------------------
app.py — Handles the entire user interface. Manages file upload, session state, and question presentation flow using Streamlit widgets.
resume_parser.py — The intelligence layer for document understanding. Reads raw resume text and extracts structured data: skills lists, project titles and descriptions, job roles, and durations.
interview_engine.py — Takes the parsed resume data and generates contextual questions across three categories: technical depth questions (based on listed skills), project walkthrough questions (based on described projects), and behavioral questions (based on work history).


✨ Key Features
-----------------
Resume Upload — Accepts both .pdf and .txt resume formats for broad compatibility.
Intelligent Parsing — Extracts skills, projects, and experience from unstructured resume text.
Personalized Questions — All questions are derived from the candidate's actual resume content.
Realistic Simulation — Questions are presented one at a time, mimicking a real interview format.
Immediate Feedback — Candidates receive basic feedback after each response to reinforce learning.


🚀 Getting Started
Prerequisites

Python 3.7 or higher
pip

Installation
bash# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/AbhiramSharma/AI-Interview-Simulator.git
cd AI-Interview-Simulator

# 2. Install dependencies
pip install streamlit PyPDF2

# 3. Launch the app
streamlit run app.py
The app will open in your browser at http://localhost:8501.

💡 Design Decisions
Why Streamlit?
Streamlit allows rapid development of data and ML-adjacent web apps purely in Python, removing the need for a separate frontend. This kept the project focused on core logic rather than UI boilerplate.
Why PyPDF2?
It is a lightweight, dependency-free pure-Python library well-suited for extracting text from standard PDF resumes without requiring system-level tools.
Why keep it modular?
Separating parsing (resume_parser.py) from question generation (interview_engine.py) makes each component independently testable and replaceable — for example, swapping in an LLM-based parser in a future iteration.

🔮 Future Scope
----------------
Integrate a large language model (LLM) for more nuanced, context-aware question generation
Add voice input/output for a fully spoken interview simulation
Score candidate responses using NLP-based evaluation
Support for multiple interview types: HR, technical, system design
Export interview session report as PDF


